events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — C.J. McCollum scored 14 of his 30 points in the third quarter and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame Ja Morant’s 36-point effort to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 113-102 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Pelicans beat Grizzlies without injured Williamson

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic was a little confused reacting to a key 3-pointer that helped Dallas avoid a loss after blowing a 25-point lead against Paul George and the Los Angeles Clippers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs blow big lead, hang on to beat Clippers 103-101

events.name: New York Knicks at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 25 points and eight assists as the New York Knicks beat Utah 118-111 on Tuesday night and handed the Jazz their first home loss of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson, Knicks send Jazz to third straight loss 118-111

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored 29 points and the Portland Trail Blazers rallied to beat the San Antonio Spurs 117-110 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant has 29 points, Trail Blazers rally to beat Spurs

headlines.description: — Terence Davis scored 31 points off the bench and sparked a big second-quarter run that helped the Sacramento Kings race past the New Jersey Nets 153-121 on Tuesday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings race past Nets 153-121 for 4th straight win
